                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Brigadier
                        General <persName type="to">Henry A. Byroade</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-26">26 May
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>775. Be prepared to move advance section of your Headquarters to Changchun
                    immediately on receiving clearance from me, and notice that field at Changchun
                    can safely receive planes.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
